[17.915, "o", "\u001b[92m────────────────────────────────────────────── \u001b[0m\u001b[1;34mnitpick review\u001b[0m\u001b[92m ──────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[34m╭─\u001b[0m\u001b[34m───────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[34m Summary \u001b[0m\u001b[34m────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[34m─╮\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[34m│\u001b[0m Wraps the Anthropic API to perform code review, handling authentication, rate limiting, and JSON         \u001b[34m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[34m│\u001b[0m extraction from the model's response.                                                                    \u001b[34m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[34m╰──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1m  Score  \u001b[0m\u001b[1;7;33m  6 / 10  \u001b[0m                                                                                         \r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[31m╭─\u001b[0m\u001b[31m───────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[31m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;31mBugs\u001b[0m\u001b[31m (3) \u001b[0m\u001b[31m───────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[31m─╮\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                          \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[1m \u001b[0m\u001b[1mSev       \u001b[0m\u001b[1m \u001b[0m \u001b[1m \u001b[0m\u001b[1mLine  \u001b[0m\u001b[1m \u001b[0m \u001b[1m \u001b[0m\u001b[1mIssue                                                                         \u001b[0m\u001b[1m \u001b[0m  \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────"]
[0.000, "o", "─  \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m   \u001b[1;7;31m HIGH     \u001b[0m   —        The markdown fence stripping logic is fragile. After splitting on the first      \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         newline, the code checks if `raw` ends with triple backticks, but                \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         `raw.rfind('```')` could match an embedded triple-backtick sequence inside the   \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         JSON body rather than the closing fence. This would silently corrupt the JSON    \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         payload. Use a proper regex like `re.sub(r'^```[\\w]*\\n', '', raw)` and           \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         `re.sub(r'\\n```$', '', raw)` instead.                                            \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m   \u001b[7;33m MEDIUM   \u001b[0m   —        `response.content[0].text` will raise an `IndexError` if `content` is empty,     \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         and an `Attribut"]
[0.000, "o", "eError` if the first content block is not a text block (e.g.,    \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         a tool-use block). Neither case is caught, resulting in an unhandled exception   \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         surfaced to the caller instead of a `ReviewError`. Guard with a check on         \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         `response.content` length and `response.content[0].type`.                        \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m   \u001b[7;36m LOW      \u001b[0m   —        `anthropic.APIError` is the base class for `AuthenticationError` and             \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         `RateLimitError`. Because Python evaluates `except` clauses in order, the more   \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         specific clauses are already unreachable if the base class appeared first.       \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         Here the order is correct, but if anyone reorders these handlers the specific    \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m                         cases will silently fall into the generic handler. Consider catching             \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         `anthropic.APIStatusError` for the generic case, or add a comment warning        \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                         about the ordering dependency.                                                   \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                          \u001b[31m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m╰──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\u001b[33m╭─\u001b[0m\u001b[33m───────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[33m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;33mStyle Issues\u001b[0m\u001b[33m (2) \u001b[0m\u001b[33m───────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[33m─╮\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                          \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m  \u001b[1m \u001b[0m\u001b[1mLine  \u001b[0m\u001b[1m \u001b[0m \u001b[1m \u001b[0m\u001b[1mIssue                                                                                      \u001b[0m\u001b[1m \u001b[0m  \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────  \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m   —   "]
[0.000, "o", "     The `mode` parameter is accepted but never used inside this function — it is presumably       \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m            forwarded via `build_messages`. This is fine, but there is no type annotation on the return   \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m            type beyond `dict`. A `TypedDict` or at minimum `dict` would communicate the expected         \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m            schema to callers.                                                                            \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m   —        The inline comments are verbose to the point of explaining things that are self-evident       \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m            from the code (e.g., the `cache_control` comment). Reserve inline comments for genuinely      \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m            non-obvious decisions.                                                                        \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                       "]
[0.000, "o", "   \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m╰──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[36m╭─\u001b[0m\u001b[36m─────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[36m \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36mSuggestions\u001b[0m\u001b[36m \u001b[0m\u001b[36m──────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[36m─╮\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m│\u001b[0m   • Consider adding a retry mechanism (e.g., via `tenacity`) for transient `anthropic.APIError`          \u001b[36m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m│\u001b[0m subclasses such as `InternalServerError` or `APITimeoutError`, rather than immediately surfacing them as \u001b[36m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m│\u001b[0m fatal `ReviewError` exceptions. Rate limit errors especially benefit from exponential backoff.           \u001b[36m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m│\u001b[0m   • Validate the parsed JSON against an expected schema (e.g., using `pydantic` or a manual key-presence \u001b[36m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m│\u001b[0m check) before returning it. Right now, a structurally valid but semantically wrong JSON object (missing  \u001b[36m│\u001b"]
[0.000, "o", "[0m\r\n\u001b[36m│\u001b[0m required keys) will propagate silently to the caller.                                                    \u001b[36m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m│\u001b[0m   • The `MODEL` constant is set to a specific version string. Consider documenting in a comment whether  \u001b[36m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m│\u001b[0m this should be pinned or updated, and whether callers should be able to override it. Hardcoding a        \u001b[36m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m│\u001b[0m version string can cause silent behavior changes if the model alias is redirected server-side.           \u001b[36m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m╰──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[92m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
